en_876871_0	The Government has taken initiatives to increase the tax for cigarettes.
en_876871_1	Accordingly the tax will be increased from one rupee and sixty cents to six rupees and fifteen cents depending on the length of the cigarettes.
en_876871_2	It will be effective from the first of this month.
en_876871_3	Treasury has issued a notice in this regard under the Excise regulations.
en_876871_4	The Government has increased the cigarette tax in proportion to the reduction of the Value Added Tax and the Nation Building Tax.
en_876871_5	However, the Ceylon Tobacco Company said that there would be no price increase in the cigarettes.
en_876871_6	The Government recently took a decision to reduce VAT from 15 percent to eight percent and also withdraw the Nation Building Tax for local goods.
